net.openhft.chronicle.core.jlbh

Interface JLBHTask


  • public interface JLBHTask
    Interface for tasks using the JLBH framework.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      default void complete()
      This method is used for any clean up that might be required by the benchmark.

    • Method Detail

      • init

        void init(JLBH jlbh)
        This method is called before the benchmark is started. It gives the task a chance to do initialisation.
        Parameters:
        jlbh - A reference to the JLBH which is needed so that jlbh.sample() can be invoked when the benchmark is complete. It can also be used to create more probes into the benchamrk.

      • run

        void run(long startTimeNS)
        This method is called for each iteration of the benchmark. The timestamp passed into the method is not the same as System.nanoTime(). It is the calculated time that the test is supposed to have started.
        Parameters:
        startTimeNS - The time that should be used as the start time for the sample.

      • warmedUp

        default void warmedUp()
        Notify that warmup phase is over

      • complete

        default void complete()
        This method is used for any clean up that might be required by the benchmark.
